11/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Two bilateral co-operation agreements -- one on enhancing bilateral military relations, and the other on halting the spread of weapons of mass destruction -- were signed during US Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld's visit Monday (11 October). After decorating four Macedonian soldiers for bravery and for their contributions to the anti-terror coalition, Rumsfeld met with President Branko Crvenkovski and Prime Minister Hari Kostov. Rumsfeld's next stop in the region is Romania. (Makfax, Rompres - 11/10/04)
